22/06/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The US-based Council of Better Business Bureaus has granted a license to Romania to open the first Better Business Bureau outside North America, the organisation announced Tuesday (21 June). 
George Copos, state minister for business and small and medium size enterprises, said the move would be welcomed by consumers and firms and would complement the government's efforts to maintain a fair business environment. 
(Newswire - 21/06/05)
